      `}),a.jsxs("main",{className:"page narrow",children:[a.jsx("h1",{className:"about-title",children:"About Mission Phoenix"}),a.jsx("div",{className:"about-sep"}),a.jsxs("section",{className:"about-sec",children:[a.jsx("h2",{children:"The mission"}),a.jsx("p",{children:"Mission Phoenix is a life mission to spread awareness of the real cost of pornography. A beacon of light for those already in the darkness, and a commitment to helping steer the next generation away from it."}),a.jsx("p",{children:"The name comes from the phoenix: death and rebirth. Death of your old, weak self. Rebirth of someone stronger, more confident, more alive. Someone who reclaims their soul."})]}),a.jsxs("section",{className:"about-sec",children:[a.jsx("h2",{children:"Who I am"}),a.jsx("div",{className:"about-portrait",children:a.jsx("img",{src:"/me.png",alt:"Michael"})}),a.jsx("p",{children:"My name is Michael. I'm 41 years old and was addicted to pornography since I was around 10. I still remember the first time I watched real internet porn on a dial-up modem. It took 5+ minutes to load a single image, and the rush was beyond anything I had ever experienced at that age. It was my first hit of that legal drug called pornography."}),a.jsx("p",{children:'No one ever told me about any potential harm. Sure, the magazines had an age limit and were hidden in stores, but no one told me why. Even today, kids rarely get educated on the "why" behind age restrictions on sexual content.'}),a.jsx("p",{children:"From there, it was video games, neglecting school, neglecting real relationships. My brain had a limitless supply of naked women through pixels. Why would I need real connection? My home was chaos my whole upbringing. Internet and pornography became an incredible real-life escapism utility for me."})]}),a.jsxs("section",{className:"about-sec",children:[a.jsx("h2",{children:"The darkness"}),a.jsx("p",{children:"I experienced addiction with almost every type of drug: alcohol, benzodiazepines, amphetamines, nicotine, gambling, gaming, and porn. I lived on welfare, had massive debt, decaying health, tooth decay from a decade of not seeing a dentist, a fatty liver, and no will to live. My body and organs were slowly giving up on me."}),a.jsx("p",{children:'Through all of this, pornography was the one constant. It was always there. No psychiatrist ever asked about it. I saw depression and pornography as separate things. Porn made me feel good. Depression was just something I "had." I did not link the two together.'}),a.jsx("p",{children:"There is no end to the darkness you can bathe yourself in when it comes to porn-induced fetishes, the novelty that your brain searches for in order to reach a better and better kick."})]}),a.jsxs("section",{className:"about-sec",children:[a.jsx("h2",{children:"The first rebirth"}),a.jsx("p",{children:"When I found NoFap around 10 years ago, through some survival instinct kicking in as I was almost literally decaying to my death, my first real upward spiral began. And it hit like a truck."}),a.jsx("p",{children:"I kicked addiction after addiction. Cold-turkey nicotine habits I had since 14. Cold-turkey alcohol, coffee. Started cold showers, meditation, working out. I got a job I did not deserve on paper. My colleagues were almost scared because the transformation was so intense. They all said I was a completely different person."}),a.jsx("p",{children:"It is an invisible battle that goes on every single day, but the results are not invisible. Your confidence and your level-ups show on you. You exude victory, strength, discipline, when you overcome your inner demons. Just as you exude shame, darkness, and secrecy when you do the opposite. A creep in the dark will always be a creep in the light."})]}),a.jsxs("section",{className:"about-sec",children:[a.jsx("h2",{children:"The fall"}),a.jsx("p",{children:'But I got complacent. My brain tricked me that I had "made it." I could handle inviting the demons back in and slay them at will, right? Nothing bad happens when you watch porn once or twice. But your life philosophy that dictates that choice will eventually compound enough to affect you very negatively, and spread into every other area of your life.'}),a.jsx("p",{children:"I went back to pills, amphetamines, alcohol, spending. On one trip to Spain I spent around $25,000 in 3-4 days. Money I did not have. Money I had loaned. I lost my job, my apartment, everything I had built."})]}),a.jsxs("section",{className:"about-sec",children:[a.jsx("h2",{children:"Where I am now"}),a.jsx("p",{children:"I am no longer using porn. I am no longer using any drugs. I have completely cold-turkeyed every single substance. I run every day, work out every other day, and meditate 30 minutes minimum per day. I could not even run 100 meters a few months ago due to my amphetamine-battered heart. Now I am closing in on running 10km continuously."}),a.jsx("p",{children:"I am on a debt restructuring program, which means my debt will be completely paid off in 5 years. During these 5 years I will live on existential minimum and work on my life mission both privately and professionally. I am currently in an education program under Erik Sundby, CEO of DBK Sverige, a sexual addiction clinic."}),a.jsx("p",{children:"Despite everything, I feel more motivated, more driven, and more at peace than I have ever been in my entire life. Because I have a purpose bigger than myself."})]}),a.jsxs("section",{className:"about-sec",children:[a.jsx("h2",{children:"Why this burns in me"}),a.jsx("p",{children:"I spent an estimated 30,000 to 40,000+ hours in darkness and pornography. Out of every drug I cold-turkey quit, out of every challenge I have faced, kicking the porn habit was by far the number one hardest. Because it was so deeply rooted, so incredibly accessible at any time, and you trick yourself into thinking it is a private thing that is harmless. But you have no idea how much it shows on you publicly, and the real cost of it."}),a.jsx("p",{children:"Such immense pleasure for free does not come without a real cost. It kills your motivation, your drive, your brain, your soul. And it shows in your eyes, whether you believe it or not. It shows in your presence, your everything."}),a.jsx("p",{children:'I see the immense need for someone to be the light and guide for the younger generation. This addiction is "underrated" in how dangerous it truly is. I want to make something positive out of all my years in darkness. Every mistake I have made can potentially fill a legitimate purpose: to help others avoid the same fate.'})]}),a.jsxs("section",{className:"about-sec",children:[a.jsx("h2",{children:"The philosophy"}),a.jsx("p",{children:"The battle is never finished. You have to go inside your inner dungeon and scrub every shelf, every single day. Clean out the demons on a daily basis. Every day you make an active choice of not watching porn, and an active choice of doing something good for yourself or others, is a day where you forge your own life philosophy and integrate it deeper within yourself."}),a.jsx("p",{children:"The goal is that those choices become your identity. Not just forced choices, which they are in the beginning. That is how you keep your inner dungeon clean and the demons slain on a daily basis."}),a.jsx("blockquote",{className:"about-pull",children:'"Motivation comes and goes. But when you integrate something deeply within yourself and your life philosophy, it becomes a completely different weapon."'})]}),a.jsxs("section",{className:"about-sec",children:[a.jsx("h2",{children:"Recommended reading"}),a.jsxs("div",{className:"about-books",children:[a.jsxs("div",{className:"about-book",children:[a.jsx("div",{className:"bt",children:"The Slight Edge"}),a.jsx("div",{className:"ba",children:"by Jeff Olson"})]}),a.jsxs("div",{className:"about-book",children:[a.jsx("div",{className:"bt",children:"Your Brain on Porn"}),a.jsx("div",{className:"ba",children:"by Gary Wilson"})]}),a.jsxs("div",{className:"about-book",children:[a.jsx("div",{className:"bt",children:"Can't Hurt Me"}),a.jsx("div",{className:"ba",children:"by David Goggins"})]})]})]})]})]})}function Xh(){return a.jsxs(a.Fragment,{children:[a.jsx("style",{children:`
